<p>Given a <code>pattern</code> and a string <code>str</code>, find if
    <code>str</code> follows the same pattern.
</p>
<p> Here <b>follow</b> means a
    full match, such that there is a bijection between a letter in
    <code>pattern</code> and a
    <b>non-empty</b> word in <code>str</code>.
</p>
<p><b>Examples:</b><br></p>
<ol>
    <li>pattern = <code>"abba"</code>, str = <code>"dog cat cat dog"</code>
        should return true.
    </li>
    <li>pattern = <code>"abba"</code>, str = <code>"dog cat cat fish"</code>
        should return false.
    </li>
    <li>pattern = <code>"aaaa"</code>, str = <code>"dog cat cat dog"</code>
        should return false.
    </li>
    <li>pattern = <code>"abba"</code>, str = <code>"dog dog dog dog"</code>
        should return false.
    </li>
</ol>
<p></p>
<p><b>Notes:</b><br> You may assume <code>pattern</code> contains
    only lowercase letters, and <code>str</code> contains
    lowercase letters separated by a single space.
</p>
